Class SwitchNode<T,U extends T,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cf.lukasheinzl.util.SwitchNode<T,U,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - This is the type of the value to 'switch'
    U - This is the type of the value(s) to compare to ('case')
    R - This is the type if the value this 'switch' statement returns

    public class SwitchNode<T,U extends T,R>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used by the Utils.switchComplex(Object, BiFunction) method. Each Node represents a case in the switch statement.

    Lukas Heinzl

      • caseIf

        public SwitchNode<T,U,R> caseIf(U value,
                                java.util.function.Supplier<R> result)
        This method adds a case to the switch statement and returns a new node.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to compare to
        result - The supplier, that returns the result, to call when this value compares to the input value
        Returns:
        A new node that can be used to add more cases or execute this statement with the go() method

        public R go()
        This method runs this switch statement.
        Returns:
        The value that results from any match or an IllegalArgumentException if no case compares to true
